Database Schema:
Table concert: concert_id (INTEGER), stadium_id (INTEGER), year (INTEGER)
Table stadium: stadium_id (INTEGER), name (TEXT), capacity (INTEGER)

Natural Language Question:
Show stadium name and capacity for the stadium with most concerts after 2013, and sort by the number of concerts in descending order.

SQL Query Solution:
SELECT T2.name, T2.capacity FROM concert AS T1 JOIN stadium AS T2 ON T1.stadium_id = T2.stadium_id WHERE T1.year > 2013 GROUP BY T2.stadium_id ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1
